<h3>Heat &amp; Cold</h3>
Olivier Deschenes and Enrico Moretti (2009)[ref]Olivier Deschenes and Enrico Moretti (2009) â€“ Extreme Weather Events, Mortality, And Migration. The Review of Economics and Statistics, November 2009, 91(4): 659â€“681. Online at <a href="http://www.econ.ucsb.edu/~olivier/DM_RESTAT_2009.pdf">UCSB here</a>.[/ref] study the effect of extreme weather on life expectancy in the US. The authors ï¬nd that "both extreme heat and cold result in immediate increases in mortality. The increase in mortality following extreme heat appears mostly driven by near-term displacement, while the increase in mortality following extreme cold is long lasting."
